# Time Keeper — Pi Context

## Mission
Time Keeper is a self-hosted personal work-timer PWA for tracking time by category, reviewing weekly summaries, and producing Workday-friendly totals.

## Stack
- Frontend: React + Vite + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
- Backend: Node.js + Express + Drizzle ORM
- Database: SQLite
- Auth: Authentik embedded outpost via NPM forward auth
- Package manager: Yarn 4 workspaces

## Primary source of truth
- `AGENTS.md` — session bootstrap and standing documentation requirements
- `docs/memory/INDEX.md` — project map and task routing
- `docs/memory/invariants.md` — hard architectural rules
- `docs/memory/decisions.md` — ADR log
- `SECURITY.md` — security posture and dependency audit status

## Critical code paths
- `packages/backend/src/db/schema.ts`
- `packages/backend/src/middleware/auth.ts`
- `packages/shared/src/utils/rounding.ts`
- `packages/backend/src/services/summaryService.ts`
- `packages/frontend/src/components/WeeklySummary.tsx`
- `packages/frontend/src/components/CategoryManager.tsx`
- `packages/frontend/src/components/WeeklyGoalSetting.tsx`

## Verification commands
- `yarn workspace @time-keeper/shared test`
- `yarn workspace @time-keeper/backend test`
- `yarn workspace @time-keeper/frontend test`
- `yarn workspace @time-keeper/backend build`
- `yarn workspace @time-keeper/frontend build`

## Documentation sync triggers
- Dependencies/API/auth/storage changes -> `SECURITY.md`
- Dev workflow/tooling/process changes -> `CONTRIBUTING.md`
- Visible feature or setup changes -> `README.md`
